---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Pairs Trading Dashboard">
  <section class="dashboard-shell">
    <h1 class="dashboard-title">Statistical Arbitrage Analysis for Pairs Trading of SHOP (TSX) and SHOP (NASDAQ)</h1>
    <p class="dashboard-intro">
    Rolling-window pairs strategy over the last two years of SHOP data. The first chart overlays SHOP.TO with SHOP converted to CAD and maps signal thresholds back into implied SHOP.TO price bands; the second shows cumulative, mark-to-market,  PnL in CAD.
      <br><br>
      Green marks a long leg, red marks a short leg, and black marks an exit.
      <br><br>
      Each entry uses $1000 gross exposure: $500 per leg, sized using CAD-equivalent prices. 
      <br><br>
      Fees, slippage, borrow costs, and FX execution are not included.
    </p>

    <div class="controls" aria-label="Dashboard controls">
      <label>
        <span>Lookback (days) <output id="lookback-value">60</output></span>
        <input id="lookback" type="range" min="20" max="90" step="1" value="60" />
      </label>

      <label>
        <span>Entry z-score <output id="entry-value">2.0</output></span>
        <input id="entry-z" type="range" min="1" max="3" step="0.1" value="2" />
      </label>

      <label>
        <span>Exit z-score <output id="exit-value">0.5</output></span>
        <input id="exit-z" type="range" min="0" max="0.8" step="0.1" value="0.5" />
      </label>
    </div>

    <div id="dashboard-error" class="dashboard-error" hidden></div>
    <div id="band-chart" class="chart-card"></div>
    <div id="pnl-chart" class="chart-card"></div>
  </section>

  <script>
    import "../scripts/dashboard.js";
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
